# Changelog

All notable changes to Dreema will be documented in this file.

The format is based on Keep a Changelog and follows Semantic Versioning.

---

## [0.1.0] - 2026-06-05

### Added

#### Core Framework

- Initial release of Dreema.
- ASGI-based asynchronous application engine.
- Application lifecycle management with startup and shutdown hooks.
- Global application context for shared services and resources.

#### Routing

- Static route registration.
- Dynamic route parameter support.
- Route grouping utilities.
- Route dispatching and request resolution.

#### Requests & Responses

- Request abstraction for accessing:
  - Request body
  - Query parameters
  - Path parameters
  - Headers
  - HTTP method
  - Authenticated user

- Standardized JSON response format.
- Custom status code and message handling.

#### Database & ORM

- Built-in ORM.
- Database connection management.
- Multiple database switch.
- Model definition support.
- Query builder.
- Migration support.

#### Authentication & Security

- Custom authentication handler registration.
- Request-level user resolution.
- Security utility foundations.

#### CLI

- Project scaffolding.
- Model generation.
- Application bootstrap commands.
- Version tracking support.

#### Configuration

- Environment-based configuration loading.
- Application registry system.
- Custom code and message extensions.

#### Project Structure

- Standardized MVC architecture:
  - Controllers
  - Models
  - Views

- Endpoint-based route registration.
- Framework metadata tracking via `.dreema.json`.

### Notes

- This release establishes the core architecture and development workflow for Dreema.
- Future releases will focus on validation, middleware, caching, scheduling, storage management, testing utilities, and package distribution.
